{"_id":"8CTmhMvQ5BJlGD2o","name":"Heretical Priest","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"class","data":{"abilities":"<p>Insightful, roll 3d6+2 for Presence. Frail, roll 3d6-2 for Strength. Roll a d8 on the weapons table and may use Powers while wearing medium armor. You begin with one of the following:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Sacred shepherd&rsquo;s crook</li>\n<li>Stolen Mitre</li>\n<li>List of Sins</li>\n<li>The Blasphemous Nechrubel Bible</li>\n<li>Stones taken from Thel-Emas' Lost Temple</li>\n<li>(Wrong Jesus) Crucifix</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Unholy Origins</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Galgenbeck, near the cathedral of the Two-Headed Basilisks.</li>\n<li>Massacred Alli&aacute;ns cult, sole survivor.</li>\n<li>The crypts of Grift.</li>\n<li>Temple ruins in the Valley if the Unfortunate Undead.</li>\n<li>One of the many Graven-Tosk thief-tunnels.</li>\n<li>Secret Bergen Chrypt church.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","armorTableDie":"1d4","description":"Hunted by the Two-Headed Basilisks of the One True Faith, this heretic can be found raving in ruins, traipsing endlessly down dusty roads and desecrating cathedrals by night.","omenDie":"1d4","startingAgility":"3d6","startingHitPoints":"1d8","startingItems":"morkborg.class-heretical-priest,Armored Caster","startingPresence":"3d6+2","startingRolls":"morkborg.rolls-heretical-priest,Heretical Priest Items,1\nmorkborg.rolls-heretical-priest,Unholy origins,1","startingSilver":"3d6*10","startingStrength":"3d6-2","startingToughness":"3d6","weaponTableDie":"1d8"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/tokens/players/heretical_priest.png","effects":[]}
{"name":"Sacred shepherd’s crook","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>Its head a hook of human bone inscribed with overlapping anti-prayers. This crook hooks through other worlds. Staff does 2d4 damage except to faithless humans.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1,"damageDie":"2d4","handed":"2","weaponType":"melee"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/shepherds-crook.png","effects":[],"_id":"OzdhtFbwwJNMk1py"}
{"name":"Stones taken from Thel-Emas’ Lost Temple","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"misc","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>Cast the stones on the ground. Their pattern reveals if danger lurks in an adjacent room. The stones can lie. The priest tests Presence DR10 to see if they are true but after failing they cannot test again until the sun has set.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/stones.png","effects":[],"_id":"Q5EckLsZNjsNVLc6"}
{"name":"Stolen Mitre","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"misc","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>While wearing this holy hat the priest's vile body fades, becoming hard to hit in combat (Defense DR10). If pulled over the ears outside of battle the priest becomes nearly invisible, testing stealth against DR8.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/mitre.png","effects":[],"_id":"hhCP0wkVWMjXjLGi"}
{"name":"The Blasphemous Nechrubel Bible","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"misc","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>So intensely blasphemous even the Priests themselves can only peruse it once per day. When read, roll a die.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Even result:</span> For the rest of the day PCs heal d4 HP after just five minutes of rest.</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Odd result:</span> The priest is plagued by demon hallucinations. The DM may invent d3 things that only the Priest can see and describe them to the player as if true. This effect ends with sunrise.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/blasphemousbible.png","effects":[],"_id":"lmjtliPXdk0u2zW6"}
{"name":"(MʁOИҼ ՂEƧꓵƧ) CRUCIFIX","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"misc","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>The crucifix can be used in encounters with the undead as we as lesser trolls and goblins. Check morale (add or subtract the priest's Presence modifier) to see if the creatures bow and kindly remove themselves.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/wrong-crucifix.png","effects":[],"_id":"s7IPLLQcYedhA7mI"}
{"name":"List of Sins","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"misc","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>A long and accurate document cross-referenced against reality to discover unseen evil-doers. Successfu Presence DR10: A strange light surrounds evil creatures. The list's owner defends with +2 against any being discovered this way.</p>","carryWeight":1,"equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/classitems/listofsins.png","effects":[],"_id":"tmBvT2Xa23nKQJXE"}
